==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Semi-
<hw>Sem"i-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L. <ets>semi</ets>; akin to Gr.
<?/<?/<?/, Skr. <ets>s⟦amac⟧mi</ets>-, AS. <ets>s⟦amac⟧m</ets>-, and
prob. to E. <ets>same</ets>, from the division into two parts of the
same size. Cf. <er>Hemi-</er>, <er>Sandelend</er>.]</ety> <def>A prefix
signifying <xex>half</xex>, and sometimes <xex>partly</xex> or
<xex>imperfectly</xex>; <as>as, <ex>semi</ex>annual, half yearly;
<ex>semi</ex>transparent, imperfectly transparent</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The prefix <xex>semi</xex> is joined to another word
either with the hyphen or without it. In this book the hyphen is omitted
except before a capital letter; as, <xex>semi</xex>acid,
<xex>semi</xex>aquatic, <xex>semi</xex>-Arian, <xex>semi</xex>axis,
<xex>semi</xex>calcareous.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semiacid</ent>⟦br⟧
